# Interview Question

## Which command should we use in real projects?

Answer:

> In real-world Kubernetes projects, we typically use `kubectl apply` because it supports both creation and updates and follows Kubernetes' declarative model. `kubectl create` is mainly used for one-time creation or resource generation.

---

# Quick Comparison

| Feature                   | kubectl create | kubectl apply |
| ------------------------- | -------------- | ------------- |
| Creates Resource          | Yes            | Yes           |
| Updates Existing Resource | No             | Yes           |
| Declarative               | No             | Yes           |
| Used in CI/CD             | Rarely         | Very Common   |
| Production Friendly       | No             | Yes           |

### Easy Way to Remember

```text
create = Create Only

apply = Create + Update
```

