# Interview Question

## What is the purpose of the -o flag?

Answer:

> The `-o` flag stands for Output Format. It is used to control how Kubernetes displays command output. Common formats include `wide`, `yaml`, `json`, `name`, `custom-columns`, and `jsonpath`.

